CAPE TOWN - As Parliament gears up for the State of the Nation Address, it's not yet clear if former president Jacob Zuma will be in attendance. Parliament spokesperson Moloto Mothapo says Zuma has not yet responded to his invitation. WATCH: President Jacob Zuma resigns Speaking to eNCA senior anchor Jeremy Maggs, Mothapo confirmed an invitation was sent to the former president in terms of the category of heads of state. Mothapo said, however, that the invitation was sent at the 11th hour due to the "events of the last 24 hours". Zuma resigned as president only on Wednesday night. eNCA